==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indistinctly
<hw>In`dis*tinct"ly</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n`d⟦icr⟧s*t⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧kt"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an indistinct manner; not clearly; confusedly;
dimly; <as>as, certain ideas are <ex>indistinctly</ex>
comprehended</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In its sides it was bounded distinctly, but on its ends confusedly
and <qex>indistinctly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir I. Newton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indistinctness</ent>⟦br⟧
